WEBVTT

00:00.770 --> 00:04.315
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren, and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons.

00:04.775 --> 00:09.522
This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:10.182 --> 00:18.353
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you.

00:18.473 --> 00:27.986
So get ready to be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the church.

00:31.778 --> 00:37.344
the dream of Pilate's wife, a sermon by Charles Spurgeon, part four.

00:38.766 --> 00:51.941
When he was sat down on the judgment seat, his wife sent unto him saying, Have nothing to do with that just man, for I have suffered many things this day in a dream because of him.

00:53.163 --> 00:56.807
Matthew's Gospel, chapter 27, verse 19.

00:58.749 --> 00:59.410
Thirdly,

01:00.034 --> 01:06.181
We have now the lamentable task of observing the frequent failure even of the best means.

01:07.643 --> 01:17.734
I have ventured to say that, humanly speaking, it was the best means of reaching Pilate's conscience for his wife to be led to expostulate with him.

01:18.915 --> 01:22.239
He would hear but few, but her he would hear.

01:23.340 --> 01:25.863
And yet even her warning was in vain.

01:27.185 --> 01:28.306
What was the reason?

01:30.498 --> 01:37.387
First, self-interest was involved in the matter, and that is a powerful factor.

01:38.829 --> 01:43.335
Pilate was afraid of losing his governorship.

01:43.355 --> 01:47.221
The Jews would be angry if he did not obey their cruel bidding.

01:48.002 --> 01:53.129
They might complain to Tiberius, and he would lose his lucrative position.

01:54.390 --> 02:00.178
Alas, such things as these are holding some of you captives to sin.

02:00.290 --> 02:01.191
at this moment.

02:02.632 --> 02:08.338
You cannot afford to be true and right, for it would cost too much.

02:09.579 --> 02:21.730
You know the will of the Lord, you know what is right, but you renounce Christ by putting Him off, and by abiding in the ways of sin that you may gain the wages thereof.

02:23.232 --> 02:29.938
You are afraid that to be a true Christian would involve the loss of a friend's goodwill,

02:30.818 --> 02:37.907
or the patronage of an ungodly person, or the smile of an influential worldling.

02:38.969 --> 02:40.551
And this you cannot afford.

02:41.632 --> 02:45.517
You count the cost and reckon that it is too high.

02:46.518 --> 02:50.844
You resolve to gain the world even though you lose your soul.

02:51.986 --> 02:52.526
What then?

02:53.447 --> 02:55.610
You will go to hell rich.

02:56.972 --> 02:58.514
A sorry result this.

02:59.298 --> 03:02.322
Do you see anything desirable in such an attainment?

03:03.283 --> 03:07.870
Oh, that you would consider your ways and listen to the voice of wisdom.

03:09.292 --> 03:28.498
The next reason why his wife's appeal was ineffectual was the fact that Pilate was a coward, a man with legions at his back, and yet afraid of a Jewish mob, afraid to let one poor prisoner go whom he knew to be innocent.

03:29.122 --> 03:33.908
afraid because he knew his conduct would not bear inspection.

03:35.210 --> 03:37.133
He was morally a coward.

03:38.655 --> 03:45.244
Multitudes of people go to hell because they have not the courage to fight their way to heaven.

03:46.826 --> 03:55.437
The fearful and unbelieving shall have their portion in the lake which burneth with fire and brimstone which is the second death.

03:57.240 --> 03:58.802
So, Seth, the word of God,

04:00.610 --> 04:07.579
they are afraid of encountering a fool's laugh and so rush upon everlasting contempt.

04:08.981 --> 04:23.040
They could not bear to tear themselves away from old companions and excite remarks and sarcasm among ungodly wits, and so they keep their companions and perish with them.

04:24.502 --> 04:30.450
They have not the courage to say no and swim against the stream

04:31.106 --> 04:38.355
They are such cowardly creatures that they will sooner be forever lost than face a little scorn.

04:39.457 --> 04:43.863
Yet while there was cowardice in Pilate, there was presumption too.

04:44.944 --> 04:52.914
He who was afraid of man and afraid to do right, yet dared to incur the guilt of innocent blood.

04:53.796 --> 04:58.802
O, the cowardice of Pilate, to take water and wash his hands,

04:59.138 --> 05:07.670
as if he could wash off blood with water, and then say, I am innocent of his blood, which was a lie.

05:08.631 --> 05:09.633
See ye to it.

05:10.614 --> 05:24.133
By those last words, he brought the blood upon himself, for he consigned his prisoner to their tender mercies, and they could not have laid a hand upon him unless he had given them leave.

05:25.394 --> 05:28.018
O the daring of Pilate, thus

05:28.098 --> 05:32.084
in the sight of God to commit murder and disclaim it.

05:33.205 --> 05:37.912
There is a strange mingling of cowardliness and courage about many men.

05:38.532 --> 05:46.544
They are afraid of a man, but not afraid of the eternal God who can destroy both body and soul in hell.

05:47.465 --> 05:56.978
This is why men are not saved, even when the best means are used because they are presumptuous and dare defy the Lord.

05:57.922 --> 06:01.226
Besides this, Pilate was double-minded.

06:02.207 --> 06:04.609
He had a heart and a heart.

06:05.771 --> 06:10.536
He had a heart after that which was right, for he sought to release Jesus.

06:11.817 --> 06:21.949
But he had another heart after that which was gainful, for he would not run the risk of losing his post by incurring the displeasure of the Jews.

06:23.490 --> 06:26.834
We have plenty around us who are double-minded,

06:27.458 --> 06:29.321
Many men run two ways.

06:29.942 --> 06:35.530
They seem earnest about their souls, but they are far more eager after gain or pleasure.

06:36.371 --> 06:40.457
Strange perversity of man that he should tear himself in two.

06:41.919 --> 06:50.051
We have heard of tyrants tying men to wild horses and dragging them asunder, but these people do this with themselves.

06:51.293 --> 06:54.898
They have too much conscience to neglect the Sabbath.

06:55.746 --> 07:11.312
and to forgo attendance at the house of prayer, too much conscience to be utterly irreligious, to be honestly infidel, and yet at the same time they have not enough conscience to keep them from being hypocrites.

07:12.894 --> 07:16.460
They let I dare not wait upon I would.

07:18.183 --> 07:22.290
They want to do justly, but it would be too costly.

07:23.266 --> 07:33.339
They dare not run risks, and yet meanwhile they run the awful risk of being driven forever from the presence of God to the place where hope can never come.

07:35.521 --> 07:38.825
Oh, that my words were shot as from a cannon.

07:40.047 --> 07:43.031
Oh, that they would hurl a cannon shot at indecision.

07:44.112 --> 07:52.242
Oh, that I could speak like God's own thunder, which makes the hinds to carve and breaks the rocks in pieces.

07:53.314 --> 08:09.913
even so would I warn men against these desperate evils, which thwart the efforts of mercy, so that even when the man's own wife, with tender as love, bits him escape from the wrath to come, he still chooses his own destruction.

08:10.834 --> 08:19.423
Lastly, we have a point which is yet more terrible, the overwhelming condemnation of those who thus transgress.

08:21.025 --> 08:21.906
This pilot

08:22.146 --> 08:24.149
was guilty beyond all excuse.

08:25.151 --> 08:41.055
He deliberately and of his own free will condemned the just Son of God to die, being informed that he was the Son of God and knowing both from his own examination and from his wife that he was a just person.

08:42.878 --> 08:47.145
Observe that the message which he received was most distinct.

08:48.587 --> 08:50.450
It was suggested by a dream

08:50.818 --> 08:52.880
but there is nothing dreamy about it.

08:53.621 --> 08:56.164
It is as plain as words can be put.

08:57.125 --> 09:04.993
Have nothing to do with that just man, for I have suffered many things this day in a dream because of him.

09:05.954 --> 09:12.061
He condemned the Lord with his eyes open, and that is an awful way of sinning.

09:13.703 --> 09:20.210
Oh, my dear friends, am I addressing any here who are purposing to do some very sinful thing

09:20.354 --> 09:22.817
but have lately received a warning from God?

09:24.540 --> 09:27.484
I would add one more caution.

09:27.504 --> 09:32.050
I pray you by the blessed God and by the bleeding Savior.

09:32.771 --> 09:41.323
And as you love yourself and as you love her from whom the warning may have come to you, do stop and hold your hand.

09:42.145 --> 09:44.528
Do not this abominable thing.

09:45.049 --> 09:45.970
You know better.

09:47.362 --> 09:56.952
The warning is not put to you in some mysterious and obscure way, but it comes point blank to you in unmistakable terms.

09:57.773 --> 10:06.283
God has sent conscience to you, and he has enlightened that conscience so that it speaks very plain English to you.

10:07.804 --> 10:16.914
This morning's discourse stops you on the highway of sin, puts its pistol to your ear and demands that you stand and deliver.

10:17.954 --> 10:22.601
stir an inch, and it will be at your own soul's peril.

10:23.122 --> 10:23.803
Do you hear me?

10:24.964 --> 10:28.429
Will you regard the heaven-sent expostulation?

10:29.511 --> 10:37.202
Oh, that you would stand still a while, and hear what God shall speak, while he bids you yield yourself to Christ today.

10:37.262 --> 10:43.131
It may be now or never with you, as it was with Pilate that day.

10:44.553 --> 10:45.234
He had

10:45.378 --> 10:49.603
The evil thing which he was about to do fully described to him.

10:50.645 --> 10:54.750
And therefore, if he ventured on it, his presumption would be great.

10:56.352 --> 11:03.822
His wife had not said, have nothing to do with this man, but with this just man.

11:05.224 --> 11:07.727
And that word rang in his ears.

11:08.688 --> 11:13.234
And again, and again repeated itself till he repeated it too.

11:13.762 --> 11:15.444
Read the 24th verse.

11:16.104 --> 11:22.530
When he was washing his wicked hands, he said, I am innocent of the blood of this just person.

11:23.311 --> 11:26.334
The very name his wife had given to our Lord.

11:27.395 --> 11:29.397
The arrows stuck in him.

11:30.077 --> 11:31.899
He could not shake them off.

11:33.000 --> 11:43.410
Like a wild beast, he had the javelin sticking in his side, and though he rushed into the forest of his sin, it was evidently rankling in him still.

11:43.650 --> 11:46.354
that just person haunted him.

11:47.796 --> 12:05.360
Sometimes God makes a man see sin as sin, and makes him see the darkness of it, and if he then perseveres in it, he becomes doubly guilty, and pulls down upon himself a doom intolerable beyond that of Sodom of old.

12:06.702 --> 12:12.850
Beside that, Pilate was sinning not only after distinct warning, and a warning

12:12.930 --> 12:21.542
which set out the blackness of the sin, but he was sinning after his conscience had been touched and moved through his affections.

12:22.944 --> 12:26.609
It is a dreadful thing to sin against a mother's prayer.

12:27.791 --> 12:29.053
She stands in your way.

12:29.714 --> 12:31.396
She stretches out her arms.

12:31.917 --> 12:35.962
With tears, she declares that she will block your road to position.

12:37.264 --> 12:41.330
Will you force your way to ruin over her prostrate form?

12:42.018 --> 12:47.103
She kneels, she grasps your knees, she begs you not to be lost.

12:48.905 --> 12:52.408
Are you so brutal as to trample on her love?

12:53.829 --> 12:58.374
Your little child entreats you, will you disregard her tears?

12:59.815 --> 13:08.303
Alas, she was yours, but death has removed her, and as she departed, she entreated you to follow her to heaven.

13:09.744 --> 13:11.506
And she sang her little hymn,

13:11.938 --> 13:14.681
Yes, we'll gather at the river.

13:15.762 --> 13:27.935
Will you fling your babe aside as though you were another Herod that would slay the innocents and all in order that you may curse yourself forever and be your own destroyer?

13:29.036 --> 13:31.279
It is hard for me to talk to you thus.

13:32.600 --> 13:37.906
If it is coming home to any of you, it will be very hard for you to hear it.

13:38.818 --> 13:48.550
Indeed, I hope it will be so hard that you will end it by saying I will yield to love which assails me by such tender entreaties.

13:49.771 --> 14:08.274
It will not be a piece of mere imagination if I conceive that at the last great day when Jesus sits upon the judgment seat and Pilate stands there to be judged for the deeds done in the body, that his wife will be a swift witness against him

14:08.610 --> 14:09.511
to condemn Him.

14:10.813 --> 14:24.450
I can imagine that at the last great day there will be many such scenes as that, wherein those who loved us best will bring the most weighty evidences against us if we are still in our sins.

14:26.072 --> 14:37.266
I know how it affected me as a lad when my mother, after setting before her children the way of salvation, said to us, if you refuse Christ and perish,

14:37.634 --> 14:41.819
I cannot plead in your favor and say that you were ignorant.

14:42.980 --> 14:47.285
No, but I must say, Amen, to your condemnation.

14:48.947 --> 14:50.148
I could not bear that.

14:51.890 --> 14:55.695
Would my mother say, Amen, to my condemnation?

14:56.936 --> 15:00.861
And yet, Pilate's wife, what can you do otherwise?

15:01.622 --> 15:03.504
When all must speak the truth.

15:04.385 --> 15:05.426
What can you say?

15:05.922 --> 15:14.190
but that your husband was tenderly and earnestly warned by you and yet consigned the Savior to his enemies.

15:16.292 --> 15:21.056
O my ungodly heroes, my soul goes out after you.

15:22.258 --> 15:22.998
Turn ye.

15:23.058 --> 15:24.820
Turn ye.

15:24.880 --> 15:27.082
Why will ye die?

15:28.383 --> 15:30.525
Why will ye sin against the Savior?

15:31.987 --> 15:35.410
God grant you may not reject your own salvation.

15:36.098 --> 15:48.536
but may turn to Christ and find eternal redemption in Him, whosoever believeth in Him hath everlasting life."

15:48.556 --> 15:49.838
Thank you for listening, friends.

15:50.118 --> 15:55.466
This podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

15:55.486 --> 16:03.538
